rComments: Contemporary Canada-ABP-2010- Pros:M.Hume is a good teacher. Explains a lot, takes many questions, is available for help, shares his notes, works from the textbook Cons:Talks too much, goes off topic every class, repeats himself a lot, does not follow the course syllabus, changes the dates of assign. and tests a lot, rarely gives marks above 78%

Engaging, rambling lectures that always have a point and tie in to the material for those who are up on the reading. Supportive and flexible to those who communicate with him. A fantastic teacher whose teaching style inspired me greatly. Highly recommended course, note the course is mainly history with assignments in a contemporary based context.

Micheal is a cool dude. It's inspiring to watch him do his thing. He is organized, clear, tells you exactly what he needs from you, and on top of it, he is pretty funny. Initial anxiety is a norm, just do the work, details are not as important as the context, get some feedback early and you'll be ok
Awesome teacher, would pass university with flying colors if he was my prof. for all my classes

Contemporary Canada-ABP: The previous rating is accurate.  His writing is hard to read. He can go on tangents during lectures but they're usually relevant.  I am learning how to be an effective student.  I'd highly recommend his course.

Contemporary Canada - Academic Bridging Program.  I find his teaching style engaging.  He's understanding and supportive of mature students needs & fears. Well structured heavy workload. Since it's my 1st course @ UofT I'm not comparing it to others.
